{"id":590939778,"lang":"java","time":"1Â month","timestamp":1637577290,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/590939778/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Trapping Rain Water","memory":"41.9 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int trap(int[] height) {\n        if(height == null || height.length == 0) return 0;\n        int res =0;\n        int l =1, r = height.length-2, lmax = height[0], rmax = height[height.length -1];\n        \n        while(l <= r){\n            if(lmax < rmax){\n                if(height[l] >= lmax){\n                    lmax = Math.max(height[l], lmax);\n                }else{\n                    res +=lmax - height[l];\n                }\n                l++;\n            }else{\n               if(height[r] >= rmax){\n                   rmax = Math.max(height[r], rmax);\n               }else{\n                   res+=rmax-height[r];\n               }\n                r--;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"trapping-rain-water"}
